// Bit Manipulation Concept:
//
// Bit manipulation refers to the act of algorithmically manipulating bits or binary digits
// (0 and 1) within an integer. It's used for optimization and solving problems faster.
//
// Advantages:
// - Space efficiency (uses bits directly).
// - Speed (bitwise operations are fast: AND, OR, XOR, NOT, SHIFT).
//
// Examples:
// - Checking even/odd
// - Swapping two numbers without temp variable
// - Finding single non-repeating number among pairs
